## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests

1. **Generate a small synthetic dataset** to verify the generator works:
   ```
   python dataset/generate_synthetic.py --num_chars 10 --num_words 10 --num_phrases 5
   ```
   Verify: images exist in `dataset/images/`, `labels.txt` has 25 entries, split files are populated.

2. **Dry-run the training script** (1 epoch, tiny dataset) to verify the pipeline doesn't crash:
   ```
   python training/train.py --epochs 1 --batch_size 2 --data_dir dataset --output_dir model/brahmi_trocr
   ```

3. **Run inference** on one of the generated synthetic images:
   ```
   python inference/predict.py --image dataset/images/img_000001.png --model_dir model/brahmi_trocr
   ```

> [!NOTE]
> Full training (10 epochs, 20k samples) will take significant time and GPU. The verification above uses a minimal dataset to confirm correctness only.
